    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1960-03-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-11T00:00:00-05:00"
                n="[Unnumbered document following Document 710 (#133)]" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d710a-133">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Editor’s Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>—No official record of the substance of the conversation at this meeting has been
                    found. <persName corresp="#p_TJV1">Truman</persName> states in <hi rend="italic"
                        >Year of Decisions</hi>, page 402, that at this meeting the British
                    participants were <pb facs="0671" n="477" xml:id="pg_477"/> informed of the
                    suggestion made by <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> earlier in the
                    day (see <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_476">page 476</ref>)
                    concerning a formal request to the Soviet Government to enter the <gloss
                        target="#t_War1">war</gloss> against Japan.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
